Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Our+Founding&amp;rft.pub=CLAGS&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fweb.gc.cuny.edu%2Fclags%2Fpages%2Ffounding.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMartin+Duberman\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://news.columbia.edu/content/2017-commencement-press-release\">http://news.columbia.edu/content/2017-commencement-press-release</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://sevenstories.com/books/3995-jews-queers-germans\">\"Books &#124; Seven Stories Press\"</a>. Sevenstories.com<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-04-05</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Books+%26%23124%3B+Seven+Stories+Press&amp;rft.pub=Sevenstories.com&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsevenstories.com%2Fbooks%2F3995-jews-queers-germans&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMartin+Duberman\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Martin_Duberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20121113182233/http://www.archives.ncdcr.gov/western_archives/eadxml/pc_duberman_martin.xml\">Martin Duberman Collection, 1933 - 1980</a> (15.2 cubic feet) are housed at the <a href=\"/wiki/State_Archives_of_North_Carolina\" title=\"State Archives of North Carolina\">State Archives of North Carolina</a>. Western Regional Archives.</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archives.nypl.org/mss/848\">Martin B. Duberman papers, 1917-1997</a> (41 linear feet) are housed at the <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Public_Library\" title=\"New York Public Library\">New York Public Library</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Martin_Duberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0239260/\">Martin Duberman</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/IMDb\" title=\"IMDb\">IMDb</a>&#32;</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/RagRadio2011-03-25\">Martin Duberman and David McReynolds on Rag Radio</a>, interviewed by <a href=\"/wiki/Thorne_Dreyer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thorne Dreyer\">Thorne Dreyer</a> (53:28)</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://theragblog.blogspot.com/2011/03/books-doug-ireland-martin-dubermans.html\">Martin Duberman's <i>A Saving Remnant</i> reviewed by Doug Ireland on <i>The Rag Blog</i></a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.c-span.org/person/?martinduberman\">Appearances</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/C-SPAN\" title=\"C-SPAN\">C-SPAN</a></li>\n<li>Duberman and his work have been written about in a number of books, including Herbert Livesey, \"The Professors (1975), Paul Russell, \"The Gay 100\" (1995), Michael Bronski, \"Outstanding Lives\" (1995), Paul Berman, \"A Tale of Two Utopias\", Paul Cain, \"Leading the